U.S. President Joe Biden arrived in Mexico on Sunday ahead of the North American Leaders' Summit. Biden arrived at Mexico City's new international airport, Felipe Angeles, where he was welcomed by his Mexican counterpart Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador, after visiting the U.S.-Mexico border. Biden will be joined by Lopez Obrador and Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau in the North American Leaders' Summit scheduled for Tuesday, before which he will also hold one-to-one meetings with the two leaders. (With input from AFP)